				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="zh">基于多目标决策方法改进LCA 的污染场地修复技术比选研究</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToDataSource>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="en">When utilizing this data set for in-situ soil remediation studies or related environmental assessments, users should ensure that the chemical characteristics of contaminants, soil composition, and existing site conditions are compatible with in-situ chemical oxidation process. It is important to consider site-specific parameters, such as the presence of subsurface utilities or building foundations, which can affect the distribution of oxidizing agents. Users must adhere to local environmental regulations concerning the application of chemicals for remediation purposes. The impact on surrounding flora and fauna, as well as long-term efficacy and potential for soil stabilization, should also be assessed as part of the methodological considerations.</useAdviceForDataSet>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="zh">在使用此数据集进行原位土壤修复研究或相关环境评估时，用户应确保被污染物的化学特性、土壤成分和现有现场条件与原位化学氧化过程相兼容。考虑现场特定参数（例如地下设施或建筑基础的存在），这些因素可能会影响氧化剂的分布，这一点很重要。用户必须遵守有关用化学品进行修复目的的当地环境法规。在方法论考虑中，还应评估对周围动植物的影响以及长期有效性和潜在的土壤稳定性。</useAdviceForDataSet>
		</dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativeness>
